In addition to the food and beverage sector, the pharmaceutical industry is also a significant end-user of xylose. Xylose is used in various pharmaceutical applications, such as drug formulation and delivery systems, due to its properties and compatibility with medicinal compounds. The pharmaceutical industry's focus on developing innovative and effective drugs is driving the demand for high-quality xylose products from reputable suppliers. Companies like Zhejiang Huakang Pharmaceutical Co. Ltd. play a crucial role in supplying pharmaceutical-grade xylose to meet the industry's stringent standards.

Moreover, the personal care products industry is another emerging sector driving the demand for xylose. Xylose is used in cosmetics and personal care products for its moisturizing and conditioning properties. With the growing consumer awareness of natural and sustainable ingredients in beauty products, the demand for xylose in this industry is expected to rise. Companies like Shandong Longlive Bio-Technology Co. Ltd., with their focus on eco-friendly solutions, are well-positioned to capitalize on this trend and provide innovative xylose formulations for personal care applications.

